0.body: My name is Vince, great to meet you! The aim of this site is to keep track of my professional career. Its contents going forwards will act as: A hub for my web presence. An up to date web format of my resume. A list of my professional interests. A blog of things I may find interesting. A source of personal documentation. Feel free to navigate around with the sidebar and to reach out if you want to get in contact!
0.title: Welcome

1.body: Here you can find a summary of my positions in descending chronological order. The goal is to provide a better storytelling format than a standard PDF resume.
1.title: Resume

10.body: Tenure: Summer 2020 internship Tech: Python · C/C++ · RTOS · BDD During my second university internship, I was assigned to the Dream Chaser Communications Subsystem (DCCS) project destined for SNC and NASA. My tasks were composed of behavior driven development in Python and flight software development in C/C++. I had the chance to learn about real time OS simulators, payloads/configurations of military standard buses, and ISS/C2V2 communication protocols.
10.title: Software Developper

12.body: Tenure: Summer 2019 internship Tech: C# · SQL · TDD During my first university internship, I joined a team responsible for internal and client tool development for the automation industry. My main mandate was application development in C# that delt with high throughput SQL management and proprietary cloud platforms in XML.
12.title: Software Developper

14.body: Tenure: Summer 2017 Tech: C#, Test benches, Hardware/Software R&D My first professional internship took place in college, I took on a technician role which involved validation of optical transport platforms before samples would be approved for larger scale production. My work requried physical assembly of devices as well as reverse engineering products and processes obtained via a company acquisition.
14.title: New Products Introduction Technician

15.body: As my professional software engineering career progresses, I have found myself slowly drifting towards tackling complex problems in backend spaces. This is also my comfort zone when taking on hobby projects! My main regions of interest gravitate around the following domains: Distributed systems Databases and data pipelines Cloud infrastructure Software architecture Monitoring and observability
15.title: Interests

19.body: The document you are currently reading is an attempt I am making to archive some of my thoughts during my professional career. You may call it a blog or a progress log. I will be considering it a semi-organized mess.

20.body: This site should help me remember some interesting tidbits while working in tech. These may be technical discoveries or simply internal monologue that I would like to preserve. Subjects may be relevant to the following domains (hopefully?): Backend software Event-driven systems CLIs and SDKs Architecture DevSecOps Data pipelines Cloud infrastructure

21.title: Any particular structure ? ⭡

22.body: The current iteration of this blog is built on mdbook , which is the same documentation tool used for the Rust book. I messed around with Hugo a bit, yet didn't find it to be barebones enough for my needs. The simplicity and ease of maintenance provided by this crate should help me update and redact posts without too much hassle!

22.title: Why this look and feel ? ⭡

3.body: Tenure: January 2024 - Present Tech: AWS · GCP · OAuth · GitHub Apps · Kubernetes With the emergence of a new DevEx division, I was selected to seed a team focused on enhancing the developer experience around Snyk's PR review integrations. Alongside this, I kept the responsibility of partnering on development of Snyk's Slack integration and event-driven AWS offerings. The overall objective being to reduce friction of security tooling and operations as the company shifts into the enterprise space.
3.title: Software Engineer (Developper Experience)

4.body: Tenure: August 2023 - January 2024 Tech: AWS · GCP · OAuth · Kafka · Go · PostgreSQL Having the opportunity for internal mobility, I took on a lateral move to join a core Platform Engineering team focused on extending the Snyk Apps offering to internal and external clients. This included collaboration on various initiatives for third party integrations, authentication, cloud based event-driven systems, webhooks, and API tooling. I also had the chance to take on once more the additional responsibility of the security champion role for this team.
4.title: Software Engineer (Platform Engineering)

5.body: Tenure: January 2023 - August 2023 Tech: GCP · Kubernetes · ArgoCD · OpenAPI · PostgreSQL Following a promotion, I continued working as an engineer in a Growth team. My work was focused on helping the team shift left while ensuring key features improved the user acquisition and retention funnels. This involved refining my technical skills in DevSecOps, cloud infrastructure, observability, and data systems. I had the opportunity to take on additional involvement as a security champion within the company and participated in an API focus group to feed knowledge and best practices back into the team.
5.title: Software Engineer (Growth Engineering)

6.body: Tenure: May 2022 - January 2023 Tech: Kubernetes · OpenAPI · CircleCI · PostgreSQL · TypeScript · DDD For my first permanent job out of university, I was hired into Snyk. In this position, I filled in a Backend/DevOps role in an R&D team focused on monetization and billing of SaaS offerings. The main challenges were technical scoping and architecture for monolith feature decomposition in a distributed ecosystem.
6.title: Associate Software Engineer (Monetization)

8.body: Tenure: Summer 2021 internship Tech: AWS · Python · TypeScript · React · Redis · Snowflake During my third university internship, I joined Spiria in two different teams. In the first team I was tasked with modernization of the web platforms at the core of the company. This included backend architecture, API design, and DevOps implementations. In the second team, I led the frontend development to deliver a country wide grant and funding platform serving over 1000 organizations for an external client.
8.title: Software Developper
